@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - usageapi/Schedule
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Schedule spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetSchedule;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListSchedules using filters name;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateSchedule\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteSchedule with required\nvia GetSchedule or ListSchedules to DELETED\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetSchedule or\nListSchedules until OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id, name, query_properties,\nsaved_report_id (+2 more);
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateSchedule only for mutable fields\ndefined_tags, description, freeform_tags,\noutput_file_format (+1 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: usageapi
slug: schedule
kind: Schedule
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: defined_tags, description,
freeform_tags, output_file_format (+1 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, name, query_properties,
saved_report_id (+2 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_usage_schedules filters name
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The generated runtime reuses an existing
schedule by listing on the required
compartmentId request scope plus the exact
schedule name, then binding on that unique name
before GetSchedule loads the full payload for
drift evaluation.
The Usage API exposes lifecycleState on Schedule
bodies, so create and update settle without a
service-local synchronous wrapper; both ACTIVE
and INACTIVE are modeled as steady
resource-exists states.
In-place updates are limited to description,
outputFileFormat, resultLocation, freeformTags,
and definedTags; name, compartmentId,
scheduleRecurrences, timeScheduled,
savedReportId, and queryProperties require
replacement and are rejected before OCI
mutation.
Delete retains the finalizer until GetSchedule
confirms the schedule no longer exists.
end note
@enduml
